<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<object type="traktor.mcp.SkillAsset">
	<name>create-mesh-from-geometry</name>
	<description>Author a render mesh from procedurally generated vertices via create_mesh_from_geometry.</description>
	<whenToUse><![CDATA[Need a custom mesh from generated geometry (winding, UVs, textured material, static or skinned).]]></whenToUse>
	<body><![CDATA[# Create a render mesh from raw geometry

Author a static (or skinned) render mesh "{{name}}" from procedurally generated vertices with `create_mesh_from_geometry`, material "{{material}}".

## Tool arguments
- `path`, `fileName` (writes a `.tmd` under `Assets/`), `guid` (reused on re-run ‚Üí the asset guid stays stable).
- `positions` `[[x,y,z]‚Ä¶]`, `polygons` `[[i0,i1,i2,(i3)]‚Ä¶]` (quads or tris), `normals` (optional ‚Äî computed if omitted), `texCoords` `[[u,v]‚Ä¶]` (parallel to `positions`).
- `material` (model-material name), `triangulate: true`.
- `maps` `{diffuse, normal, roughness, specular, metalness, emissive ‚Üí value}` ‚Äî declares named material maps (requires `texCoords`). A **texture guid** embeds the texture in the model; an **empty string `""`** declares a named-but-unbound map to bind on the MeshAsset instead (preferred ‚Äî see below).
- `meshType`: `"static"` (default) or `"skinned"` (add `joints`, `jointIndices`, `animations`).

Then `build_asset {guid, rebuild:true, wait:true}`.

## Bind textures on the asset (preferred)
Bind textures on the MeshAsset rather than baking them into the `.tmd`, so the model can be re-skinned without rebuilding geometry:
1. Create the mesh with **unbound** slots ‚Äî `maps: { "diffuse": "" }` (with `texCoords`): a named `diffuse` map carrying no embedded texture.
2. Bind by map name on the asset ‚Äî `set_instance_member { guid:<mesh>, member:"materialTextures", value:{ "diffuse":"<texture guid>" } }`. `create_mesh_from_geometry` overwrites the asset, so set `materialTextures` **after** (re)creating the mesh, then `build_asset`. The pipeline resolves `materialTextures[name]` onto the model's matching named map at build time.

Pass a real texture **guid** in `maps` only when you deliberately want it baked into the model.

## Gotchas
- **Winding**: front face = **clockwise**. Auto-orient each quad: if `dot(cross(p1‚àíp0, p2‚àíp0), outwardNormal) > 0`, reverse the order.
- **Tiling UVs**: project world coordinates onto the face plane and divide by a tile size (X-face ‚Üí `(z,y)/tile`, Y-face ‚Üí `(x,z)/tile`, Z-face ‚Üí `(x,y)/tile`) for seamless tiling across adjacent pieces.
- **Stable guid**: re-running with the same `path` + `guid` keeps the guid, so entities that reference the mesh pick up new geometry on rebuild with no scene edit.
- **Hard vs smooth edges**: give each face its own vertices with the face normal for hard edges; average normals across shared vertices for smooth ones.
- **materialTextures keys = map names**: the binding key must match the map name declared in `maps` (e.g. `diffuse`, `normal`), and the map must exist (declare it unbound with `""`) for the binding to take effect.
]]></body>
	<engineVersion/>
	<published>true</published>
	<parameters>
		<item type="traktor.mcp.SkillParameter">
			<name>name</name>
			<description>Mesh asset name</description>
			<defaultValue>Mesh</defaultValue>
		</item>
		<item type="traktor.mcp.SkillParameter">
			<name>material</name>
			<description>Material name</description>
			<defaultValue>Material</defaultValue>
		</item>
	</parameters>
</object>
